# N/A
#
# Please note that:
#  - The HEADER (first line) is a single line of max. 50 characters
#    that contains a succinct description of the change.
#    + <type> describes the kind of change, types are:
#      * feat (feature, component or screen)
#      * styl (CSS and design)
#      * test (testing)
#      * fixs (maintain)
#      * docs (documentation)
#      * rele (release)
#    + <subject> is a very short description of the change, format:
#      * imperative, present tense: “change” not “changed”/“changes”
#      * no capitalised first letter
#      * no dot (.) at the end
#  - The BODY should include the motivation for the change and
#    contrast this with previous behavior and must be phrased in
#    imperative present tense. Optional to add click up link.
#  - The FOOTER should contain any information about Breaking
#    Changes or possibly any effects on existing code. N/A otherwise.
#
# To configure this template run:
#     $git config --local commit.template ./.git-message-template